<H3> <TI>   Wen Jiabao Leaves for Bangladesh, India, Singapore </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0501034894 Beijing XINHUA in English 0310 GMT 5 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0501034894 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, January 5 (XINHUA) -- A Chinese Communist 
Party delegation headed by Wen Jiabao, alternate member of the 
Political Bureau and member of the Secretariat of the Central 
Committee of the Chinese Communist Party (CPC), left here today 
on an official goodwill visit to India and Bangladesh. 
  The delegation has been invited by the Indian National 
Congress (Indira Gandhi) and the Bangladesh Nationalist Party. 
  On its way to India and Bangladesh, the delegation will also 
visit Singapore at the invitation of its government. 
  Among those who saw the delegation off at the airport were 
Li 
Shuzheng, alternate member of the CPC Central Committee and head 
of the International Liaison Department of the CPC Central 
Committee, and the diplomatic envoys of the three countries in 
China. 

