<F P=100> Central Eurasia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Azerbaijan's Foreign Minister Visits </TI></H3>
<H4>   Received by Li Peng </H4>
<F P=102> OW0501121394 Beijing XINHUA in English 1158 GMT 5 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0501121394 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, January 5 (XINHUA) -- Chinese Premier Li 
Peng said here today that China attaches great importance to its 
relations with Azerbaijan and is looking forward to a visit to 
China by Azerbaijan President Geydar Aliyev. 
  "The exchange of visits by high-level officials will surely 
promote the development of our bilateral ties," Li told visiting 
Azerbaijan Foreign Minister Gasan Gasanov and his party here 
this afternoon. 
  In response, Gasanov said his country gives priority to its 
ties with China and that President Aliyev is keen to visit China. 
  China and Azerbaijan are both Asian countries and the 
friendly contacts between the two peoples date back to the "silk 
road" period of 2000 years ago, Li noted. 
  Recalling his visit to Azerbaijan some 40 years ago, Li said 
his memory of that visit is as fresh as ever, and the Baku 
oilfield is well known among the Chinese people. 
  Li noted that the Chinese government gave Azerbaijan prompt 
recognition after it gained independence, and the two countries 
soon established ambassadorial-level diplomatic ties. 
  "For the past two years our bilateral relations have marked 
steady and healthy development. I am satisfied with that," the 
Chinese premier said. 
  During the meeting Gasanov conveyed to Li the regards from 
President Aliyev to Chinese President Jiang Zemin and other 
Chinese leaders. 
  The current Azerbaijan-China ties are good, Gasanov said, 
adding that his country is willing to co-operate with China in 
every field. 
  He also expressed his admiration for the progress China has 
made through reforms while maintaining its stability. 

</TEXT>

