<H3> <TI>   Reports on U.S. Textile Import Quota </TI></H3>
<H4>   `Serious Protest' Issued </H4>
<F P=102> OW0701102594 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 0727 
GMT 7 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW0701102594 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Chinese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, 7 Jan (XINHUA) -- A spokesman of the 
Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation today said 
that If the U.S. side clings obstinately to its course [yi yi gu 
xing 0001 1942 1324 5887] on the bilateral trade of textile 
products, China will be compelled to take appropriate 
retaliatory measures. 
  The spokesmen today issued a statement to lodge a serious 
protest [yan zhong kang yi 0917 6850 2123 6231] against the 
United States' unilateral move to cut import quota of textiles 
from China. 
  The Sino-U.S. bilateral agreement on textile products 
expired 
on 31 December 1993. The two sides held three rounds of talks 
prior to the expiration date but could not reach an agreement. 
  The spokesman said: When the two sides are about to hold the 
fourth round of talks, the U.S. side unilaterally declared sharp 
cuts in import quota of textiles from China. "This is a very 
irresponsible move. It has not only aroused strong reaction 
[qiang lie fan ying 1730 3525 0646 2019] in China but also 
generated extensive dissatisfaction [guang fan bu man 1639 3131 
0008 3341] in the United States. It will seriously influence 
[yan zhong ying xiang 0917 6850 1758 0742] the economic and 
trade relations between China and the United States." 
  He said: The Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic 
Cooperation solemnly [zheng zhong 6774 6850] declares that the 
Chinese side will continue the talks according to the original 
plan and solve the problem through negotiations. If the U.S. 
side clings obstinately to its course, China will be compelled 
[po 6612] to take appropriate retaliatory measures[bao fu cuo 
shi 1032 1788 2238 2457]. 

</TEXT>

