<F P=103> OW0601143194 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Singapore, January 6 (XINHUA) -- Wen Jiabao, 
alternate member of the Political Bureau of the Central 
Committee of the Communist Party of China (CPC), today called on 
Singapore Deputy Prime Minister Lee Hsieng Loong. 
  Wen, who is leading an eight-member CPC delegation, arrived 
here Wednesday [5 January] night for a two-day visit at the 
invitation of Lee Hsieng Loong. 
  During the meeting, Lee told Wen that Singapore was happy to 
see that China had rapidly grown in economy due to its reforms 
and open-door policy. The Asia-Pacific region has always 
benefited from China's prosperity and stability. 
  Wen Jiabao said that the relationship between China and 
Singapore is getting closer in recent years and both sides 
cooperated well in many areas and at higher levels. 
  He said that the three visits paid by Senior Minister Lee 
Kuan Yew in 1993 marked the new development in the relationship 
between the two countries. 
  The Chinse delegation also visited the Port Authority of 
Singapore and the Jurong industrial township today. 
  Wen Jiabao is scheduled to call on Prime Minister Goh Chok 
Tong and Senior Minister Lee Kuan Yew Friday. 

