<F P=100> Southeast Asia &amp; Pacific </F>
<H3> <TI>   Sino-Vietnamese Trade Fair To Open 25 April </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0601032994 Beijing XINHUA in English 0246 GMT 6 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0601032994 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Nanning, January 6 (XINHUA) -- The first 
Sino-Vietnamese trade fair, to take place on April 25, will be 
held simultaneously in the Tunghsing Development Zone in south 
China's Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region and Mong Cai County in 
northeast Vietnam. 
  An executive of the Tunghsing Development Zone said the fair 
is sponsored by the management commission of the zone, the 
Guangxi Academy of Social Sciences and Vietnam's Mong Cai County. 
  During the fair, 20 to 30 experts, scholars and professional 
executives from both sides will exchange economic reform 
experiences and discuss the prospects for bilateral economic and 
technical cooperation as well as the prospects for regional 
economic development in the border areas of the two countries. 
  Business communities of the two countries will hold talks on 
economic and technical cooperation. More than 280 Vietnamese 
firms have expressed their readiness to cooperate with Chinese 
counterparts. Some 500 Chinese companies, mainly from China's 
relatively developed areas, will attend the fair. 
  Business people from around the world are expected to 
conduct 
talks on investment projects in the region. 
  The fair will also organize commodity exhibitions. Both 
China and Vietnam will organize groups to exchange visits. 
  According to latest official statistics, the border trade 
volume in the Tunghsing Development Zone exceeded 200 million 
yuan (about 23 million U.S. dollars) in 1993. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

