<F P=100> NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political &amp; Social </F>
<H3> <TI>   Li Peng, State Council Examine Draft Labor Law </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0701103394 Beijing XINHUA in English 1014 GMT 7 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0701103394 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, January 7 (XINHUA) -- Chinese Premier Li 
Peng presided over the 14th executive meeting of the State 
Council in Beijing today to examine a draft law on labor and a 
set of draft regulations on overseas financial agencies in China. 
  The draft law of labor is designed to meet the development 
of 
the socialist market economy, to protect the legal rights and 
interests of workers and regulate labor relations in China. 
  The draft regulations on the management of overseas 
financial 
agencies in China are aimed at improving management and 
supervision measures in this field. 
  The conference approved the two draft documents in 
principle. 
After further revision, the draft law on labor will be submitted 
to the Standing Committee of the National People's Congress for 
deliberation. The regulations on the management of overseas 
financial agencies will be promulgated by the State Council 
after further revision. 

</TEXT>

