<F P=100> REGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> East Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Shanghai Adopts Residence Measure for Investors </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  HK0701032694 Beijing ZHONGGUO XINWEN SHE in English 1422 GMT 
6 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK0701032694 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing ZHONGGUO XINWEN SHE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Shanghai, January 6 (CNS)--Overseas investors or 
those from Hong Kong, Macao or Taiwan who have made an 
investment of at least U.S.$200,000 here, have had their items 
or their businesses operating for more than two years in the 
municipality will be qualified to apply for special residential 
status from next month. 
  This measure states that people from elsewhere in the 
Mainland with RMB [renminbi] 1 million worth of investment in 
the municipality and have had their items or businesses 
operating for more than two years may also apply for such 
residential status. 
  Other qualified applicants include overseas people who have 
bought a housing unit specially for overseas buyers measuring 
over 100 sq. metres and Mainland personnel hired by a particular 
Shanghai entity for at least three years. 
  The regulation stipulates that people with this special 
residential status have to renew it annually with the municipal 
public security department. Following such renewals after 
certain years, the provisional residential status may be changed 
to permanent residential status. 
  People with such residential status can have their spouse 
and 
children apply for the same status provided that they meet the 
requirements. They will enjoy the same treatment in their daily 
living as all other Shanghai residents including being able to 
send their children to a child care centre and receive a general 
education, applying for a business licence and the installation 
of gas and telephone. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

