<F P=100> REGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> East Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Shanghai To Accelerate Coastal Development </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0701100294 Beijing XINHUA in English 0822 GMT 7 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0701100294 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Shanghai, January 7 (XINHUA) -- Shanghai city in 
east China has formulated a plan for accelerating development on 
coastal waters. 
  The plan notes that Shanghai now has a land area of 6,340.5 
square kilometers, but its coastal waters cover 7,226 square 
kilometers. 
  "The Shanghai Marine Development Plan" constitutes a major 
part of Shanghai's current urban planning, it says. 
  By the year 2000, the proportion of the gross output value 
of 
the marine economy in Shanghai in the total output value in the 
city will rise by 0.5 to 1 percent [figures as received]. 
  The focus of the development plan is on the coastal belts 
and 
nearby waters, involving opening up of oil and gas projects, 
manufacturing of oceanic medicines, underwater projects and 
surveying for mineral resources on the sea floor. 

</TEXT>

