<F P=100> Military </F>
<H3> <TI>   Military Increases Exchanges With Foreign Nations </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0701085594 Beijing XINHUA in English 0803 GMT 7 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0701085594 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, January 7 (XINHUA) -- The Chinese armed 
services have exchanged more visits with their counterparts in 
other countries, according to an official of the Ministry of 
National Defense. 
  The official said that last year the armed services received 
120 visiting groups from more than 40 countries and regions, and 
sent some 60 groups abroad. 
  During the past 15 years, the Chinese military have received 
tens of thousands of foreign military and political leaders. 
  Some of the well-known Chinese military institutes, such as 
the Academy of Military Science of the Chinese PLA [People's 
Liberation Army] and the National Defense University, have 
established broad contacts with relevant foreign organizations 
for academic exchanges. 

</TEXT>

