<H3> <TI>   Jiang Zemin Signs Various Presidential Decrees </TI></H3>
<H4>   Further on Accounting Law Amendment </H4>
<F P=102> OW0601134994 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 0219 
GMT 30 Dec 93 </F>

<F P=103> OW0601134994 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Chinese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By reporters Liu Siyang (0491 1835 2254) and Zhang Yinshu </F>
(1728 6892 2562)] 
  [Text] Beijing, 30 Dec (XINHUA) -- The Fifth Session of 
the Eighth National People's Congress [NPC] Standing Committee, 
which ended yesterday, has adopted a "decision of the NPC 
Standing Committee on amendment of 'Accounting Law of the 
People's Republic of China.'" According to the decision, the 
Accounting Law which has been implemented for eight years will 
be partially amended. 
  President Jiang Zemin yesterday signed presidential decree 
No. 17 promulgating the "decision." According to it, the law 
will contain 30 articles in six chapters after the amendment. 
Some experts concerned have pointed out that the amendment of 
the Accounting Law will play an important role in perfecting the 
accounting system, maintaining market economic order, and 
improving China's investment environment. 

</TEXT>

