<H3> <TI>   Jiang Zemin Signs Various Presidential Decrees </TI></H3>
<H4>   Further on Company Law </H4>
<F P=102> OW0601123894 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 0230 
GMT 30 Dec 93 </F>

<F P=103> OW0601123894 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Chinese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, 30 Dec (XINHUA) -- President Jiang Zemin 
yesterday signed Presidential Decree No. 16 promulgating 
"Company Law of the People's Republic of China." According to 
the presidential decree, the law was adopted by the Fifth 
Session of the Eighth National People's Congress Standing 
Committee of the People's Republic of China on 29 December 1993, 
and it will become effective on 1 July 1994. 
  The Company Law has 11 chapters -- general provisions; the 
establishment and organizations of limited liability company; 
the establishment and organizations of company limited by 
shares; share issuance and transfer of company limited by 
shares; corporate bonds and debentures; corporate finance and 
accounting; corporate merger and division; corporate bankruptcy, 
disbandment and liquidation; branch of foreign company; legal 
liability; and supplementary provisions. 

</TEXT>

