<F P=100> Economic &amp; Agricultural </F>
<H3> <TI>   Metallurgical Industry Attracts Foreign Investment </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  HK0601140194 Beijing ZHONGGUO XINWEN SHE in English 0910 GMT 
6 Jan 93 </F>

<F P=103> HK0601140194 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing ZHONGGUO XINWEN SHE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, January 6 (CNS)--China's metallurgical 
industry received U.S.$900 million of foreign investment last 
year with direct investment by foreign businessmen of U.S.$150 
million, according to the Ministry of Metallurgical Industry. 
  Foreign government loans were given to expansion projects of 
the Baoshan iron and Steel Company, the Wuhan Iron and Steel 
Company and the Daye Steel Works expansion project in Hubei 
province and the seamless steel project of the Anshan Iron and 
Steel Company. U.S.$500 million was raised from the issuance of 
H stocks in Hong Kong by the Maanshan Iron and Steel 
Shareholding Company. China has also made progress in its 
cooperation in the exploitation of mines with Brazil, Mongolia 
and South Africa with more than 30 million tonnes of ore being 
imported to China. 
  China has also developed and cultivated its internal market 
for iron and steel products with such markets in Tianjin and 
Guangdong now operating. The state has further eased price 
controls over iron and steel products with such products whose 
prices were set by the state being reduced to three million 
tonnes and those under the control of the state mandatory plan 
dropping from 20.8 million tonnes to 15 million tonnes. 

</TEXT>

