<F P=100> Central-South Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Guangxi Registers Growth in Commodity Sales </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  HK0601085894 Nanning Guangxi People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 1130 GMT 26 Dec 93 </F>

<F P=103> HK0601085894 </F>
<F P=104>  Nanning Guangxi People's Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Mandarin </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] In the course of seizing the opportunity to develop 
their economies, different localities in Guangxi have paid 
attention to commodity sales. Commodity sales in various 
localities are thriving amid stability. In society, commodity 
sales have seen a comparatively large increase. According to 
statistics, from January to November, Guangxi registered an 
increase of 20.8 percent over last year in total commodity 
sales. Five cities registered commodity sales increases of more 
than 23 percent. The total retail sale volumes of 
Fangchenggang, Beihai, and Nanning increased by 48 percent, 34.9 
percent, and 33 percent respectively. There were varying 
increases in commodity sales in the eight prefectures of the 
region, with Guilin, Wuzhou, and Yulin registering growth rates 
higher than Guangxi's average. 

</TEXT>

