<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] New Delhi, January 7 (XINHUA) -- A delegation of 
the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China (CPC) led 
by Wen Jiabao, an alternate member of the Political Bureau of 
the CPC Central Committee and secretary of its Secretariat, 
arrived here tonight for a six-day goodwill visit to India. 
  During the visit which is at the invitation of the Indian 
National Congress Party (I), Wen is scheduled to meet Indian 
Congress Party leaders, Prime Minister P. V. Narasimha Rao and 
other senior government officials and exchange views with them 
on further development of relations between the two parties and 
the two countries. 
  Sushil Kumar Shindhi, general secretary of Indian National 
Congress Party visited China in July 1993. 
  It is the fifth visit of the CPC delegation to India since 
the establishment of relations between the two parties in 1985 
and is also the most high ranking CPC delegation to visit India 
in recent years. 

